<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Setup ==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
1. Open FreeCAD and create a new empty document with {{MenuCommand|File → [[File:Std_New.svg|16px]] [[Std_New|New Document]]}}.
:1.1. Switch to the [[Part_Workbench|Part Workbench]] either with {{MenuCommand|View → Workbench → [[File:Workbench_Part.svg|16px]] [[Part_Workbench|Part Workbench]]}}, or with the [[Std_Workbench|Workbench Selector]] [[File:Std_Workbench_ComboBox_Icons_And_Text.png|x16px]]. 
:1.2. Press the {{Button|[[File:Std_ViewIsometric.svg|16px]] [[Std_ViewIsometric|Isometric]]}} button, or press {{KEY|0}} in the numerical pad of your keyboard, to change the view to isometric to visualize the 3D solids better.
:1.3. Whenever you add objects, press the {{Button|[[File:Std_ViewFitAll.svg|16px]] [[Std_ViewFitAll|Fit All]]}} button, or its hotkey {{KEY|V}}, {{KEY|F}}. This will pan and zoom the [[3D_View|3D View]] so that all elements are visible in the view.
:1.4. Hold {{KEY|Ctrl}} while you click to select multiple items. If you make a wrong selected or want to de-select everything, just click in an empty area in the [[3D_View|3D View]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Create the basic shape==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
2. Create a rectangular box:
:2.1. Insert a primitive cube by clicking on {{Button|[[Image:Part_Box.svg|16px]] [[Part_Box|Cube]]}}.
:2.2. Select the created {{incode|Cube}} in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]].
:2.3. On the {{MenuCommand|Data}} tab of the [[Property_View|Property View]]:
::2.3.1. Change {{MenuCommand|Width}} to {{incode|31 mm}}.
:2.4. Re-center the view per step 1.3.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
3. Create a chamfer:
:3.1. Select the upper edge ({{incode|Edge6}}) of the elongated face of the {{incode|Cube}} in the [[3D_View|3D View]].
:3.2. Press {{Button|[[Image:Part_Chamfer.svg|16px]] [[Part_Chamfer|Chamfer]]}}.
:3.3. In the {{MenuCommand|Chamfer Edges}} [[Task_Panel|task panel]]:
::3.3.1. Verify that {{MenuCommand|Select edges}} is selected and that the {{MenuCommand|Chamfer type}} is {{incode|Equal distance}}.
::3.3.2. Change {{MenuCommand|Length}} to {{incode|5 mm}}.
::3.3.3. Press {{Button|OK}}. This will create a {{incode|Chamfer}} object.
</div>

[[File:01_T04_Part_Cube_base_long.png]]
<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Caption|Base object created from an edited cube and a chamfer operation.}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Insert the ShapeString==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
4. Create the ShapeString:
:4.1. Switch to the [[Draft_Workbench|Draft Workbench]].
:4.2. Click on {{Button|[[File:Draft_ShapeString.svg|16px]] [[Draft_ShapeString|Shape From Text]]}}.
:4.3. In the {{MenuCommand|ShapeString}} [[Task_Panel|task panel]]:
::4.3.1. Change {{MenuCommand|Text}} to {{incode|FreeCAD}}.
::4.3.2. Change {{MenuCommand|Height}} to {{incode|5 mm}}.
::4.3.3. Make sure {{MenuCommand|Font file}} points to a valid font, (e.g, {{incode|/usr/share/fonts/truetype/dejavu/DejaVuSans.ttf}} or {{incode|C:/Windows/Fonts/arial.ttf}}).
:::Note: for more details about working with fonts please refer to the [[Draft_ShapeString|Draft ShapeString]] page.
::4.3.4. Reset its location to the origin by pressing {{Button|Reset Point}}.
::4.3.5. Press {{Button|OK}}. This will create a {{incode|ShapeString}} object.
:4.4. In the [[Tree_View|Tree View]], select {{incode|Chamfer}}. On the {{MenuCommand|View}} tab, change the value of {{MenuCommand|Visibility}} to {{incode|false}}, or press {{KEY|Space}} on the keyboard. This will hide the {{incode|Chamfer}} object, so you can see the {{incode|ShapeString}} better.
:4.5. To see the ShapeString from above change the view by pressing {{Button|[[File:Std_ViewTop.svg|16px]] [[Std_ViewTop|Top]]}}, or {{KEY|2}} on the keyboard.
:4.6. To restore the view to isometric, press {{Button|[[File:Std_ViewIsometric.svg|16px]] [[Std_ViewIsometric|Isometric]]}}, or {{KEY|0}} on the keyboard.
:4.7. Reverse step 4.4 to make the {{incode|Chamfer}} object visible again.
</div>

[[File:ShapeStringEngraveTutorial_ShapeStringText.png]]
<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Caption|Text created as a ShapeString, that is, a filled compound shape on a plane}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
5. Move the ShapeString to the Chamfer:
:5.1. Make sure both the {{incode|Chamfer}} object and the {{incode|ShapeString}} object are visible in the [[3D_View|3D View]]. If one is not, select it in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]] and press {{KEY|Space}} on the keyboard.
:5.2. Switch to the [[Part_Workbench|Part Workbench]].
:5.3. In the [[Tree_View|Tree View]], select {{incode|ShapeString}}.
:5.4. Select {{MenuCommand|Part → [[File:Part_EditAttachment.svg|16px]] [[Part_EditAttachment|Attachment]]}}.
:5.5. In the 3D View, select the chamfered face of the {{incode|Chamfer}}.
:5.6. In the {{MenuCommand|Attachment}} [[Task_Panel|task panel]]: 
::5.6.1 Change the {{MenuCommand|Attachment mode}} to {{incode|Inertia 2-3}}.
::5.6.2 Press {{Button|OK}}.
:5.8. Make sure {{incode|Shapestring}} is selected in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]].
:5.9. On the {{MenuCommand|Data}} tab of the [[Property_View|Property View]]:
::5.9.1. Change {{MenuCommand|Justification}} to {{incode|Middle-Center}}.
::5.9.2. Expand the {{MenuCommand|Attachment Offset}} property node and change {{MenuCommand|Angle}} to {{incode|90.0 °}}.
</div>

[[File:ShapeStringEngraveTutorial_TextOnBlock.png]]
<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Caption|The ShapeString centered on the chamfered face}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Create the engraved text==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
6. Create a solid object from the ShapeString:
:6.1. Make sure the [[Part_Workbench|Part Workbench]] is still active.
:6.2. In the [[Tree_View|Tree View]], select {{incode|ShapeString}}, then press {{Button|[[File:Part_Extrude.svg|16px]] [[Part_Extrude|Extrude]]}}.
:6.3. In the {{MenuCommand|Extrude}} [[Task_Panel|task panel]]:
::6.3.1. In the {{MenuCommand|Direction}} section select {{incode|Along normal}}
::6.3.2. In the {{MenuCommand|Length}} section set {{MenuCommand|Along}} to {{incode|0 mm}} and {{MenuCommand|Against}} to {{incode|1 mm}}.
::6.3.3. Check the {{MenuCommand|Create solid}} option.
::6.3.4. Press {{Button|OK}}. This will create an {{incode|Extrude}} object.
:6.4. Since it has been extruded into the {{incode|Chamfer}} object, the 3D View will look the same as before. Verify the creation of a solid 3D object by temporarily making the {{incode|Chamfer}} object invisible:
::6.4.1. In [[Tree_View|Tree View]], select {{incode|Chamfer}}.
::6.4.2. Press {{KEY|Space}} to hide it. You should see a solid 3D object in the shape of the word "FreeCAD".
::6.4.3. Press {{KEY|Space}} to make the Chamfer visible again.
</div>

[[File:ShapeStringEngraveTutorial_3DText.png]]
<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Caption|The 3D text after making the Chamfer object invisible.}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
7. Engrave the text on the geometry:
:7.1. In the [[Tree_View|Tree View]] select {{incode|Chamfer}} first, and then {{incode|Extrude}}.
::Note: the order in which you select the objects is important for the cut operation. The base object must be selected first, then the object to be subtracted.
:7.2. Press {{Button|[[File:Part_Cut.svg|16px]] [[Part_Cut|Cut]]}}. This will create a {{incode|Cut}} object. This is the final object.
</div>

